[02:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'saves you time or it doesn\'t. Now, the first problem we have is this terminal chaos. We\'re running too many sessions, so we\'re switching too much. Uh brain is doing the routing internally. AOE replaces that with one view we can now'

[02:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'switch between with everything visible. Our next problem is the status blindness. You don\'t know what your agents are doing. So, we have to keep checking, right? You end up keep'

[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'checking again and again. That is just costing you more time, right? And it breaks your flow. AOE shows you running, waiting, idle, error without actually attaching anything. So, we go from guessing to actually knowing what\'s'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'happening. Then we have branch conflicts, agents stepping on each other, overriding work, and creating just a big mess. AOE uses Git worktrees where each agent gets its own branch, same repo with zero collisions. The last'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'problem here this solves is the safety. Giving agents full access can be risky. AOE adds optional Docker sandboxes. Agents can now stay contained. Your system stays safe. Plus, session survive'

[03:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'restarts. You could check from your phone if you wanted to, which is honestly kind of cool. Profiles per project and diffs built in. Now, again, this is awesome. It does not replace'

